ical and self-reflective discourses around media transformations and the visual turn in British culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnglish wit and humor, PictorialzEnglandxHistoryy18th century. 0aPrintsxSocial aspectszEnglandxHistoryy18th century. 0aPrints, EnglishzEnglandy18th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh  aHenry Fuseli.  aJames Gillray.  aJohn Thomas Smith.  aWilliam Blake.  aballad sellers.  aculture.  adark media.  adefaced pictures.  aeighteenth-century London.  agraphic satire.  amass media.  apaper.  aphantasmagoria.  aprint culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishz978311099395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2022z9783110994186oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148752775440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487527754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487527754/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099395-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-SEWb2022